</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-34_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To understand the role of HEFCW, it's essential to define some key terms:
























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Higher Education Institution (HEI)</strong> - An organisation providing higher education, such as universities and colleges.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Funding council</strong> - A body that allocates government funds to HEIs based on specific criteria.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Quality assurance </strong>- Processes and procedures in place to ensure education meets certain standards of excellence.








</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">The Role of HEFCW
