</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Quality assurance </strong>- Ensuring the quality of higher education is a core function of HEFCW. It works with the Quality Assurance Agency (QAA) to monitor and enhance the quality of education Welsh HEIs provide. This involves regular assessments and reviews to ensure institutions meet national standards.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Strategic development</strong> - HEFCW plays a strategic role in developing higher education in Wales. It supports initiatives that promote innovation, widening access, and employability. This includes funding for research projects, development programmes, and partnerships with industry.






</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-54_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for compliance
