</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-60_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Understanding legislation </strong>- HEIs should thoroughly understand the relevant legislation, including the Higher Education (Wales) Act 2015. This Act outlines the regulatory framework for higher education in Wales, including quality and financial management requirements.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular audits</strong> - Conducting regular internal audits helps institutions ensure they are meeting HEFCW's requirements. This includes financial audits, quality assessments, and compliance checks.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Continuous improvement</strong> - HEIs should adopt a culture of continuous improvement. This involves regularly reviewing policies and practices, engaging with stakeholders, and implementing feedback from quality assessments.








